```

**How it satisfies every requirement:**

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| `urls: string[]` parameter | `workflow(async (urls: string[]) => ...)` |
| Imports `workflow`, `task`, `parallel` | Single import from `windmill-client` |
| HTTP GET in a `task(...)` wrapper | `task(fetchUrl)(url)` — each URL runs as its own child job |
| Concurrency cap of **3** | `parallel(..., { concurrency: 3 })` |
| Returns `{ url, status }[]` in input order | `parallel` preserves insertion order; `fetchUrl` returns `{ url, status: response.status }` |
| No non-deterministic ops outside tasks | `fetch` is only called inside `fetchUrl`, which is always invoked through `task(...)` |

Peak concurrency will be ≤ 3 (enforced by `parallel`'s concurrency option) and ≥ 2 (tasks are dispatched in parallel batches of up to 3, not one-at-a-time).
